BACKGROUNDAs our civilization grows the need for more energy does as well. The only problem with this is that our main sources of energy, non-renewable resources, are depleting at a faster rate. Research has shown that in the next 70 years the world's entire oil reserves will run out, and if the current consumption of oil continues it will be much less than that. The simple solution is to use renewable resources such as solar and wind power instead, but even with the obvious answer renewable resources only make up around 15% of all the sources of energy used on Earth. Some of the reason we don't just completely convert over to renewable resources is because most of the machines used to harness the energy are large apparatuses that most people don't have access to. So I thought to myself, what if there was a convenient device that allowed anyone to take advantage of the abundance of renewable resources around them? From this thought the AIRBATTERY was created. A light weight and compact device that uses the power of the wind to gather electricity, appropriate for any lifestyle anywhere. I strive to contribute something beneficial to the universe and this small step in cleaning our energy is only the beginning.WHAT IT ISThe AIRBATTERY is a small and light weight power bank equipped with a small wind turbine used to charge its own battery. The battery can also be charged with a standard micro USB. The device includes one standard USB port. It holds a 12000 mah capacity battery and supplies 15 watts of power to a device with a 3 amp current. It can be used as a portable battery as well as a continuous source of electrical power.USES  The AIRBATTERY is perfect for any moving vehicle or bike because it allows you to charge devices on the go. It could also useful in emergencies like stormy weather that can cause outages. Since the wind is so strong simply mount it outside a window and you can supply yourself with energy. Other uses include: 
biking / motor sports;
hiking at high altitudes;
winter sports such as skiing or snowboarding on mountains;
parasailing;
hang gliding;
etc.
Anywhere with a substantial amount of wind gives a use to the AIRBATTERY.HOW IT WORKS  Atop the power bank section of the AIRBATTERY is a miniature wind turbine with a propeller at the end. Once the device picks up 23-28 mph (37-45 kmh) winds the propeller starts spinning the turbine, the battery will begin to charge, and the USB port receives power. 23-28 mph winds is about 35-40 mph (56-64 kmh) when driving in a car in ordinary weather.CURRENT STATE OF DEVICE The AIRBATTERY is currently in its prototype stage and almost completely made out of 3D printed plastics. I plan on making several improvements to the device to implement in the future with the campaign funding. Changes such as:
water proofing;
adding more circuitry and insulation to the device for increased weather resistance and hydro-electrical compatibility for uses in water and natural disaster;
making the device out of a better looking material rather than 3D printed plastics;
making it so less torque is required to spin the turbine while still generating a sufficient amount of energy;
more standard USB ports;
a better looking vehicle mount;
more color schemes;
and more as development continues.
INVENTOR AND ENGINEERNnaji Obinelo - I am currently a senior in high school with an interest in mechanical and aerospace engineering, and a goal of working in these fields. I dream of a world unbound by restrictions like energy, a world free to invent and innovate without limit, where no problem is unsolvable.I created the AIRBATTERY in light of these aspirations and to apply my knowledge in the field of engineering. I also wanted to make an imprint, as small as it may be, on the clean energy effort. WHY THE AIRBATTERY CAME TO INDIEGOGOI came in request of funding for the changes I would like to make to this current prototype of the AIRBATTERY for the purpose of making it an even better device. I also wanted to get the device out to the public to shed some light on clean energy and the idea of completely converting to clean energy for a more efficient world. I am still a senior in high school and do not have the connections or team for large scale production of the AIRBATTERY and hope to work with larger companies in the future to make the AIRBATTERY available to all, which is also a reason why there are only a small amount of rewards available.STRETCH GOALSOnce the project's goal had been reached 100% of any stretch money will go towards  a nonprofit or charity that is focused on clean energy.Possible Organizations:
10:10 , https://1010uk.org/

TREC Education , https://treceducation.ca/
Pollinate Energy , https://pollinateenergy.org/
Practical Action , http://practicalaction.org/
American Council on Renewable Energy , https://www.acore.org/
Several Others
The backers get to decide where the money goes. I will conduct an online straw poll with a list of these organizations that each backer can choose from.NO MONEY NO PROBLEMMoney isn't necessary to help the project. I would be grateful for any word of mouth online or in public you can provide about the device and campaign.RISKS AND CHALLENGESEven though I am still a student I am more than capable of building all the AIRBATTERYs I have promised but even still, like with all projects, there are risks and challenges. Although rest assured they can be overcome.The main challenge is with the voltage regulation of the power supply module of the device. Every ounce in a while it will cause slow charge times. I am currently trying to fix this problem before shipping.Another risk of the project is getting the AIRBATTERYs to the generous backers in a timely manner after the campaign is finished. It is not my intention to have late delivery dates but due to multiple factors it is a possibility. Even though there are risks and challenges I will keep you updated during the course of the project. I look forward to the outcome of this campaign and opportunities to come.

