   GeneralInputsOutputsInternal  Once the goal is reached, we will go directly into the production phase and fulfill perk orders as soon as we can.MONEY-BACK GUARANTEEYour Order will arrive in the month indicated on the perk you claim on Indiegogo or your money back! Power Your Green LifeACOPower is an established company based in Los Angeles dedicated to providing off-grid and portable power solutions to the market. The team members strive to satisfy the needs of our diverse group of customers ranging from campers, RV or boat owners, survivalists to disaster relief workers. With seven years of experience, we are confident that you will enjoy our new product and we can’t wait to hear what you think!  Where We ShipWe're able to ship worldwide to the United States, Canada, Mexico, European Union, Australia, Japan, South Korea, Singapore, and Hong Kong. VAT and GST is included. If you live outside of the USA, Shipping cost will be applied (free for USA).When We Start ShippingThe first units will leave from factory starting Apr 2018. US & Canada backers can expect to receive your PEGASUS starting in May 2018. Other backers can expect the International version of PEGASUS to arrive starting in June 2018. Why Pre-Order NowYou'll be providing valuable feedback that will help us improve our products in the future. By pre-ordering today, you're supporting a world less dependent on gas and more on renewable energy.  GeneralWhat is PEGASUS?PEGASUS is a portable power station that can be used as a mobile power source or an emergency power source. It can be used anywhere you go and is rechargeable by soar panels, cars and outlets.Who created it?The team at ACOPower have been in the solar power business over 12 years. We saw a demand from our customers for portable power stations and PEGASUS is the result.What are the different ports and lights?Pegasus is equipped with a total of 4×USB ports (1×Quick Charge, 1×Type-C), 2×AC Output, 2×DC 6mm outputs, 1×12V car port, 1×LED light panel, and 1× LED flashlight.What sets Pegasus apart?The Battery Management System (BMS) inside PEGASUS not only regulates temperature for best performance but it also tracks the power consumption from individual ports which is shown on the LED screen in real-time.TechnicalHow do I charge my PEGASUS?PEGASUS has two input ports, one for solar charging and one for wall or car charging. They are located on the left-hand side of the PEGASUS. Solar charging takes 5-8 hours, wall charging takes 9 hours and car charging takes 13 hours.Can I use PEGASUS while it’s charging?Yes! PEGASUS can output power while being charged.Will my country's power plug be supported?Yes! We do plan on making units with 220V and 230V outputs with Universal plugs. Depending on the demand, we will release other versions as well. Please contact us if interested!  How do I store PEGASUS?To prolong battery life, PEGASUS should be fully charged before storing at room temperature away from humidity.How do I use it?Simply press the On/Off button and wait for the LED screen to respond. Once its turned on, select which ports you will be using and turn their power on individually and start charging!What is the acceptable temperature range? For optimum performance, Pegasus should be charged from 32 – 113°F (0 – 45°C) and operated from 14 – 140°F (-10 – 60°C).ShippingWhen does shipping begin?Shipping will begin in April 2018. US & Canada  backers should expect their units in starting in May. UK, EU, Australia, Japan, South Korea, Hong Kong, and Singapore will ship by June.Where does it ship to?We ship to US, Canada, Mexico, UK, EU, Australia, Japan, Singapore, South Korea, and Hong Kong. Shipping is free to the USA.  Customer ServiceWhat is the warranty?For US purchases, ACOPOWER warrants PEGASUS to be free of manufacturing defects. ACOPOWER will pay for repair or replacement of parts and labor for 18 months from the date you receive PEGASUS. Specific terms are shipped with PEGASUS.What is your pre-order refund policy?If you change your mind or change addresses, we'll do our best to accommodate. We won't able to refund Indiegogo orders once they've shipped to you.What is your return policy?Don't return PEGASUS Power Station to the store. You'll be able to contact ACOPOWER directly with any questions or concerns you might have. Specific terms are shipped with PEGASUS.Contact of customer serviceSales Inquires: Sales@ACOPower.com, +1-626-575 7722Wholesale:  B2B@ACOPower.com, +1-626 575 8822Technical Support: Support@ACOPower.comCompany Website: www.ACOPower.comPegasus Website: www.PegasusGenerator.com
